<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Gesture Step Monitor</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto:300,400,700&display=swap">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        #step-count {
            font-size: 2em;
            color: #4CAF50;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        .button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            margin: 5px;
            font-size: 1em;
            cursor: pointer;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: #fff;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        .button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
        #analytics {
            margin-top: 20px;
            display: none;
        }
    </style>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "urn:goose.ai:schema",
  "@type": "GooseApp",
  "name": "gesture-step-monitor",
  "description": "Track and visualize steps using hand movement gestures with mock data.",
  "width": 800,
  "height": 600,
  "resizable": true,
  "mcpServers": [
    "apps"
  ]
}
  </script>
  <script type="application/x-goose-prd">
A step tracker app that tracks user steps and utilizes mock data for testing purposes. The app will feature hand movement tracking capabilities to record steps. Key features include: 1. User interface displaying step count. 2. Visualization of steps taken using hand movement gestures. 3. A mock data generator for simulating step counts. 4. Options to start, pause, and reset the step tracking. 5. Basic analytics on user steps over time.
  </script>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Gesture Step Monitor</h1>
    <div id="step-count">Steps: 0</div>
    <button class="button" id="start-button">Start</button>
    <button class="button" id="pause-button">Pause</button>
    <button class="button" id="reset-button">Reset</button>
    <div id="analytics"></div>

    <script>
        let stepCount = 0;
        let isTracking = false;
        let interval;

        document.getElementById('start-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
            if (!isTracking) {
                isTracking = true;
                stepCount = 0;
                updateStepCount();
                interval = setInterval(generateMockSteps, 1000);
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('pause-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
            if (isTracking) {
                clearInterval(interval);
                isTracking = false;
                showAnalytics();
            }
        });

        document.getElementById('reset-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
            clearInterval(interval);
            isTracking = false;
            stepCount = 0;
            updateStepCount();
            document.getElementById('analytics').style.display = 'none';
        });

        function generateMockSteps() {
            const mockSteps = Math.floor(Math.random() * 5) + 1;  // Simulates 1 to 5 steps
            stepCount += mockSteps;
            updateStepCount();
        }

        function updateStepCount() {
            document.getElementById('step-count').innerText = 'Steps: ' + stepCount;
        }

        function showAnalytics() {
            const analyticsDiv = document.getElementById('analytics');
            analyticsDiv.style.display = 'block';
            analyticsDiv.innerText = 'Total Steps: ' + stepCount;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>